Dialogs.Dialog: You like rock and punk, ▲小早川＊▲？
I'd love to go into the whole rock and punk thing... and, what？
You don't want to try doing yourself, like having a band？
I see, you're not really interested in instruments or anything？
I may have told you before, but... I bought a guitar a long time ago, but I stopped right away.
I'd love to do it again if I had the chance...
Peace is good, but don't slack off. There are a lot of users today.
Yeah, yeah, I'll do what I can.
The less work you do, the more trouble you cause me...
You too, senpai... You've just been talking to Kobayakawa-san since a while ago...
Ah, geez, I get it. I'll go.
...a girl this age with a boyfriend... abominable.
You know what, if you have something to say, just say it.
...if I have something to say！？ ...what do you mean... n-no, I think... it's abominable...
Em... um... there's people waiting... everyone do your work... sorry...
Excuse me！ I'm looking for the receptionist！
This is why... the two of you are... abominable...
(It's kind of crowded... library is thriving, this school serious or not...)
Oh, hi senpai. Um, how are you and Rinko doing lately？
Hey, don't say anything unnecessary, okay？
Unnecessary, huh... like the lover's kind？
Heh, you seem to get along well.
Oh, um... what should we do... um...
There you are, Hara-chin. I heard you were in the library, so I looked for you♪
Hey, hey, isn't she like... a Library Committee member？
You know, thick glasses～ long skirts～ honeycomb braids～ like that？
S-So sorry... U-um, if you make too much noise...
Wow, so tall. It's kind of powerful...
S-So sorry... um, say... s-so sorry....
You know... let's just go, okay？
Hey, don't make a scene in the library.
Hey, I thought Hara-chin is good friends with Kobayakawa-san...
Um, it's not that... Rinko is fine, but... Rinko's friends lately, they're a little glummy...
Hey, what are you doing？ Quiet in the library！
You guys are not supposed to be making a big deal out of this.
Is it about the thing in the library the other day？
Your friend's name was... Hana-chan, right, ▲小早川＊▲？
I didn't think they were that heartless. I mean, with all those gals！
...it's frustrating when your friends make fun of you like that, isn't it？
I didn't know Hara-chan felt that way.
That girl has a lot going on in front of her gal buddy to. I bet... right？
(I hope it doesn't turn into a fight or something.)
(Well, it's another day at the Library Committee！)
(Everyone is kind of gloomy about what happened before...)
Homeroom teachers are terrible, aren't they？ Isn't it normal to stay in the classroom and dabble？
Yes, I don't know why we are being kicked out.
Hahaha！ And I'm not even in character！
E-Excuse me. S-Sorry... just that... you know...
Excuse me. The library is for everyone's use, so could you please be quiet？
If everyone uses it, why not us too？
That's why I told you to be quiet. Your noisy chatter is disturbing my reading！ Don't you get it？
Um... look, we can't stay here forever, so why don't we go to karaoke？
Hah, today was less of a hassle.
Hey, aren't you two frustrated？ You've been bullied the whole time.
Ah, geez, let's have our revenge！ Doesn't it bother you？ Don't you have the spirit of rock！？
Library committee members are gloomy and weak！ What a self-serving assumption, you know, just show them something to change that！
Is that the soul of rock？ Playing music？
I didn't mean that... rock is about awareness！
...oh, hmmm... but music might not be a bad idea... music... Rock... like a band？
What's wrong, Nagakura. Please let her speak, ▲小早川＊▲.
I-I'm sorry... I'm not a rocker, but... I played drums in a brass band when I was in middle school, though...
Seriously？ I mean, you're not what it seems... Oh, you mean like new music？
Hehe, no reason... just your image？
It doesn't matter, that's not the point. It doesn't feel good.
Now, now！ But still, you all have instrumental experience, that's awesome！
I'm sure you can do it, you're being so gullible.
I can handle it！ Okay... then it's settled！
Hey... let's band！ Are you serious？
Of course！ I'm going to surprise you and Hara-chan！
To surprise me... is that supposed to be fun？
How can you make punk just for fun？
I didn't mean that, but... music, you know, it needs spirituality. Spirituality.
Ah, geez, I'm so angry！ I'll put feelings like that into the music.
(Well, it's another day on the Library Committee...)
(By the way, I wonder what you're going to do about the band you mentioned last time, ▲小早川＊▲...)
Okay！ Then, we're going to have a band meeting, so get together！
You are also involved, so be present.
Um... what kind of band are we talking about？
Of course, it will be punk.
Of course, it's decided to be punk？
Because Rinko... I mean me said so...
Ack！ No, you see, I just thought about it a lot... and it was better to be a punk band.
Oh, I see. That explains why you play the guitar...
W-What... Masashi Sada is not g-glummy！
Oh, um... is punk different from rock or metal？
Different, huh？ Not even close, okay？ In the first place, Punk is――
Stop！ You can skip the explanation.
Hey, don't you have to make a lot of decisions if you are going to do this punk thing？
(...both of you are surprisingly willing to do it？)
What about vocals？ Will you do it Kobayakawa-san？
Hmm... that doesn't sound bad, but... while playing, I just...
Besides, it's Punk, so it's got to be a male vocalist.
Heh, you mean a girl band with only the vocalist being a guy！
Yeah. And since we're going to all this trouble, I'd like to have all the members of the Library Committee.
It's kind of literary, isn't it？ Intellectual, subversive punk, that's cool.
I-I'm sorry... I'm not really understanding...
If you do not understand, that's okay. I wonder if there is anyone out there, a guy who is a member of the Library Committee and seems to have time on his hands.
I'm a Library Committee member, and I have a lot of free time...
That's fine, it's easier than looking for someone you don't know. I can't imagine a guy I've never talked to...
(...will the band be okay with these members？)
What is it？ A statement of purpose？
No, it's not. Are you sure you want me to be there？
Hey. Don't complain about what's been decided.
Since you are going to be a punk from now on, you should be sharp.
Why are you getting so involved with those two like that？ It's a little unusual for you, ▲小早川＊▲.
Well, because neither of them says what they want to say. When I don't talk, I don't know what they're thinking.
When I see something like that, it reminds me of myself... you know.
Okay, let's start the band meeting.
That's out of the blue！ ...I'm not busy, though.
What is that... why are you in charge...
What, are you complaining？ I'm the one who started it.
Why don't you take charge of it？
No, I don't want to do that. It's a pain in the ass...
I-I'm sorry... um, don't be mad both of you...
I guess the first step is to decide on the parts. Who will play which instrument？
I told you... I used to play guitar...
That's fine. You can only play acoustic guitar, right？ Then it's the same.
Wait a sec. Then what is Sasaki-san going to play, ▲小早川＊▲？
See, she says she's going to do it.
And the band's goal is "Live at the London Million Club！".
What's with that... you should take it seriously...
I know, I know. Well, why don't we play it safe and do it at a neighborhood liho？
Live house. Have you at least been there？
Now, now！ But isn't a live house... kind of a high hurdle？ I mean, they're going to pay to come and see you.
No！ That's absolutely impossible... absolutely impossible.
Y-Yeah？ I've been wanting to try it... I guess it's tough indeed.
Oh... I remember a friend of mine from the light music club...
Our light music club has regular concerts in the auditorium... and from time to time, individual bands that are not part of the club also perform...
Heh, I remember hearing something like that.
Hmm, an on-campus light music event..
Why do you look so dissatisfied？
It's just right for those who have never been in a band.
Maybe it's more convenient to show the gals on campus... yeah, that's great！
Targets set！ We'll be at the Light Music Club's live event！
Now what, why are you so confident...
Hey, Rinko-san. Recently... you don't seem to be hanging out with me much, do you？
Yup... just for a while, I started something new.
Wow, that's cool. Did you get into the light music club？
No, with the members of the Library Committee.
...Hey, Rinko. The other day... You know, in the library.
...it's just a thought, but... those gals, I don't think they would be a good fit for you, Hara-chan.
Hmm. They are nice girls to talk to, why don't you make friends with them, Rinko？
Lost something？ You want me to go back and get it？
No, I'm talking about the band. The band name！
A band name？ Oh, I see... that's the kind of thing we have to decide on.
Of course. A good band has a cool name.
Heh. Well, shall we all meet again to decide？
Nope, I don't think such a thing can be decided easily even if a large group of people discuss it.
That may be true, but at least a little bit of everyone's――
I'm kinda picturing it. But I can't seem to get it right... hehehe.
Hey, I've been thinking a lot about this.
Band name. See, I have written it down. Which one of these would you like？
I'd go with this one... ▲バンド＊▲！
In the Rye... huh？ Yeah, I knew it. Nice！
The Dada？ That's what you chose... well, it's okay.
Towano Librarians？ That was a throw away idea... well, okay.
Rinko n' the Stupids！？ ...is this kind of thing even possible？ Well... okay.
(I suppose we can't decide on our own...)
Well, I'm sorry to keep you waiting. I have an important announcement to make.
What is it, all of a sudden.
The name of the band has been decided.
Wait a minute, why do you decide such things on your own？
Why do you have to decide？ Nagakura-senpai, say something to her...
Me？ Well, you know, I'm not particularly... s-sorry
See, then Nagakura-senpai agrees... and even him agrees with me.
Me？ I'm not saying I agree...
...this is why boyfriends are... and now a lovers' band together？ Next I will celebrate your marriage... what the hell... ah, abominable...
Ugh... ah, geez, for heaven's sake.
The band is called In the Rye！
The band is called The Dada！
The band is called Towano Librarians！
The band is called Rinko n' the Stupids！
Hmm, so I'm next, huh？ Actually, I was thinking――
What should we do about instruments and stuff？ I don't mind... but not everyone does.
I-I'm sorry... I don't have a drum set... I wonder if I could use the one from school...
I don't have a bass either.
Hah！？ Don't make it sound so easy！
Don't worry, there are cheap ones. It's punks who don't care about equipment.
As I said before, I don't know any punks...
A bass... I think my brother had a battered... *mumble*...
Yeah, that's the thing, come hang out with me for a minute.
Oh, I see, you said you had a guitar.
Yes, I did. Well, I thought I should do maintenance since I had left it alone for so long.
Okay. First show it to me！
Don't be so overzealous, do you know anything about guitars？
Let's see... in particular, the electrical system looks fine, there is some galling, but it will be fixed soon.
The frets are hardly worn, and the neck is a little forward warped, but I'll turn the rod.
Warped... Oh, oh, just that？ Just as I thought！
Yes, then we'll take care of it. The finished product will be――
Hmm, sounds like a band member to me！ I didn't quite understand what he was saying！
We haven't done anything yet... hehe, but I'm looking forward to it.
(Sounds like you're really having fun... I'll keep up the good work！)
(Well, it's another day in the band！)
What exactly do we need to do as a band？ You know, like where to practice.
Hehe, you don't have to worry about that.
Oh, sensei. How did it go？
Yeah, I got the OK. The light music club doesn't use it every day, so they said we can use it freely on their free days.
Just make sure you're doing your job as a committee member, too.
Good grief. Well, if this motivates you, then...
I asked the sensei to let our band use the music room that the light music club uses for practice.
Hehe, speed is important in these things.
(Well, it's another day in the band！)
So what are we going to do？
You can't just stand there with your instrument and do nothing...
Um... what should we do about the songs...
A song？ Oh, a song... well, why don't we start by making some sounds of our own？ Okay！
W-When we finished the meeting I was going to start！ ...Like that.
That's what I thought... a couples' band... hah～ah...
Hah, I can't believe you forgot about that...
That was not it！ I just wanted to get the whole group together to make some noise and get a feel for how things were going！
It's clear that you didn't... abominable...
I wonder about it. Aren't you a little envious？
*Ahem*！ After all, if we're going to do it, we should make it original.
Not a cover？ Who would make such a thing...
Nagakura-senpai, you were in the brass band, right？ Can't you write a song or something？
M-Me！？ I'm so sorry... I can't make it... sorry...
Impossible, huh. Then how about you, Sasaki-san？
What do you mean by "eh？" I said I wanted to not only play the guitar... I was just curious about it...
Don't worry, Sasaki-san has good grades and is very studious. If you study hard, you can compose music easily, can't you？
I'll lend you a whole set of punk classics as a reference！ Hey, please！
Please, you say... you want to do it, right？ Just do it...
...I tried it for a little bit... but it didn't work at all...
So, I was wondering if you could teach me how to compose music later...
But I'm not going to share it with you... I'm going to have you do it with a song I wrote...
Well, you're right, it's bugging me too much.
Ah, geez, I get it！ But I'll definitely write the lyrics！
(Ah... I can see you're talking with someone, ▲小早川＊▲...)
I've been a little evasive since then. Sorry.
I thought back to it right after that, and I'm kind of sorry... Hara-chan, even though it wasn't your fault.
...anyway, I don't want to get on bad terms with Hara-chan for that reason.
Even those girls are nice to hang out with...
That's still... maybe not a good idea.
I see, but I get it. Anyway, we patch things up.
(I still think it's a little awkward...)
Hey, how's it going with the lyrics？ All good？
I see... hey, let me take a look.
Why, it'll be fine. Come on！
Nope！ It's not finished yet... and it's really embarrassing to show it one-on-one. It's better to show it to everyone at once.
(Well, it's another day in the band！)
Well, I tried to make one, but...
Please don't raise the bar too high...
Here's the song anyway... w-what is it... do you have any complaints？ ...what is wrong... abominable...
Well, my eyes were not mistaken, were they？ You're good！
What's with the attitude... f-for real, do you think it's a good idea？
Sasaki-san, you're really amazing... I'm kind of impressed.
N-No way, that's such an exaggeration... *pfft*...
Oh, I want to read them.
Yeah... I knew you were good at this kind of thing, Kobayakawa-san.
In fact, I've been warming up to this kind of thing for a while now, or so I've been told at... Maybe that's why.
Um, how about... from Sasaki-san's point of view.
I think it's good... just because I got a compliment earlier, it's not like I'm returning the compliment or anything creepy like that！
...wow, I just... did a tsundere act...
But Kobayakawa-san, you are really talented.
I'm really going to cry... ugh...
Yeah, we've got some good songs and lyrics to work with... now we're ready to go full steam ahead！
Yeah... I'm so moved, even I'm impressed... Thanks, everyone.
Okay, let's practice hard from now on！
We're a little late. I wonder if those two are already there.
Eh, are there any hot guys？
Um... huh, only women... and I mean, those girls...
What... is this a band？ Seriously！？
Do you do things like rock and roll？
I don't think that's true！ They are librarians, remember？
Eh, isn't it kind of amazing？
What is it... what are you doing... you're in the way...
E-Excuse us, I-I'm sorry... we are practicing...
Oh, I'm really sorry. We interrupted you.
Both of you, shush！ I'm not complaining, you know.
...Why are you acting so high and mighty... abominable...
(You're kind of looking like a leader now, ▲小早川＊▲.)
(Well, it's another day in the band！)
Let's go to the music room.
Why do you keep acting so high and mighty...
Hey, why are you using the music room？ It's supposed to be our turn today.
I don't know about that. Besides, who are you.
I think those are ones. The advisor said. You know, the Library Committee members.
Yeah, he did say that. Don't act like you're the one renting the place. We're using it today.
Or do you want to take a tour？
Who. It's just a high school light music level anyway.
Bastards... you never heard our music to say that！
Now, now, I'm sorry！ Well... since you're here, let's watch, okay？
Well, that's just it！ We won't get in your way, just let us take a look around！
Hey, why are you goofing off？
Now, now, I don't like their attitude, but watching other bands play can be helpful.
It may be true... we are beginners, and... we have never seen an amateur band live.
We're no match for the real deal... abominable...
(Can we do a live show like these guys...？)
(Well, it's another day in the band！)
Okay, work is done. Let's practice.
Practice... well, I want to say that, but...
If we don't have a place, we can't do anything about it... What are we going to do？
It looks like the Light Music Club is using the music room again today.
Hmm... So, how about we use a studio outside？
Oh... this is a rehearsal studio！
It's kind of... out of place, isn't it？ I feel like I'm being made fun of by the people around me... abominable...
You heard the light music guys play, right？ We have to do better！
I-I see... yes... I'll do my best...
Looking more and more like a band！
Feels so good to be able to play as loud as we can！
I feel like we've improved somehow...
Yeah. I wish we had come earlier for this.
...but it costs money... it's difficult to do this too many times...
Yeah. I guess we should use the music room on the days we can use it.
This is also because of that damned Light Music Club...
(Huh... I see you're speaking with someone today ▲小早川＊▲...)
Rinko, are you still in the band？
Still, you ask... I have no plans to stop, at least not until I do some gigs.
So, you're going to do a live show？
Yes. You know the one about the Light Music sponsored event？
Oh, at least that they are doing it. I've never seen it, though.
I see. I've never seen it either... Will you come to see it？
Of course, I'll be there. I'll make a cheering flag.
Hey. How's that guitar working out for you？
Oh... yeah, well I'm still working on it.
Shut up... It's nice, the vocalist is so easygoing.
Eh？ I don't think so... well, singing can be pretty fun！
Ah, I see, that's good to know. Maybe... you're on a roll？
Do you think this might make you irresistible to girls too...？
If that's the case... a vocalist is supposed to be popular？
...you wouldn't have made it anyway, would you？
Hehe. Well, I'll do my best to work on that guitar...
I think it's coming together in its own way...
That guitar... is not good at all.
U-Um... but... if you keep practicing like this...
Sasaki-san... um, I think Kobayakawa-san practices very hard.
My left hand fingers, they're in shambles... every time I practice, I'm making a little bit more progress...
And... even my feelings about the band...
There may be some things that aren't right for you...
This song, the bass isn't that hard to play... so, I'm getting by...
...I don't want her to just run off like this, so why don't you bring her back...
Humph. This is how you get boyfriends to comfort you... abominable...
Yeah, sorry... I'll be right back.
Rinko is thinking about it, too. Maybe, it will be all right.
(I have a bad feeling about this...)
Part... you mean changing the instrument you're in charge of？
I wasn't cut out to play guitar. My hands are too small to play chords.
If it's bass, it's just a single note, no problem, right？
I've been practicing all this... and now you say that...
Sorry！ At first, I asked you to let me play guitar, but I'm sorry... Please.
...I've been practicing hard and I want this band to be a success too...
Change the part, and if it makes the band better, then...
Thank you！ I'm so sorry, Sasaki-san...
Humph. It would be a little easier if we taught each other what we've been practicing...
Hey, can I borrow your bass for a minute？
Yeah, yeah, it fits. Punk has bass, after all.
Like Shinomun, or something cool like that. Slamming on the bass with my jacket！
I also have one more request...
(Well, it's another day in the band！)
Right now... this was very good...
You there, don't water it down. All right, then, meeting！
Before this, I forgot something important.
What's with that... an outfit we're going to wear？
What's obvious... for whom is obvious... I don't have an outfit...
What kind of outfit are we going to wear？ It's a school event, so can't it be so flashy？
Boring or not, I don't need an outfit...
Yes, an outfit！ The only question is how to make them――
What's up, Nagakura？ Let's hear her, ▲小早川＊▲.
S-Sorry... outfit... um, I wonder if you can let me do them...
I'm sorry... um, it's okay if I can't... I just... I like to think about that kind of stuff... and...
Kobayakawa-san wrote the lyrics and... Sasaki-san wrote the music and... I alone... didn't get anything done.
That's not what I'm worried about... It's that guy over there that's not doing anything.
But if you could do it, that would be great. Right？
Yeah... thank you so much. Of course, I'll take everyone's input into consideration.
Hehe, of course！ I'd like to have a say in the design... oh, and I'll help you, too？
(I can't wait to see our live outfits！)
(Well, it's another day in the band！)
Okay, we'll have a meeting. Gather around.
What's happened since then to that outfit we talked about before？
Oh, that's okay. I'll do good with the girls.
This thing is, you know, no boys allowed.
Don't worry. I'll make sure to prepare one for you too. Right, senpai？
Y-Yeah... it'll be okay... it'll be okay, I guess.
So, we'll have to wait for the show to see what we'll be wearing！
(I'm curious... but it'd really add fun to the show.)
(Well, it's another day in the band！)
Hey, before practice today, why don't we have a little fun？
Hehe, that's how it is then.
This is bad, I wonder if we can make it...
Maybe not... we're going at a slow pace.
It's not our lucky day. The trains are stopping, the roads are under construction... I've made a terrible miscalculation...
You've been on a date most likely anyway. This is why boyfriends are... abominable...
As I said, I'm sorry. Come on, let's practice！
We all have to deal with your selfishness, right？ But, w-what's with that attitude...
Wait... selfishness, you said, what do you mean？ For me, everyone is...
You know, to have more fun, to say more of what you want to say, instead of just being told what to say？ And then――
But you know, we are not so pitiful...
I suppose you're still worried about what happened in the previous practice.
I'm sure Nagakura-senpai and Sasaki-san saw right through me the whole time. Rinko is just like those gals.
Sorry, it's nothing. Let's not talk about annoying things.
Um... okay, let's do it again then！
I knew I couldn't do it...
(Can we do a live show in this condition...？)
(I guess Sasaki-san and Nagakura-san have already left...)
Why do you ask that？ What do you mean...
Hmm... Sasaki-san and Nagakura-senpai, when you look at it...
It's kind of like watching the old Rinko before she met you.
It's not that we're alike. It's just that I keep to my own world. I spend my time trying not getting involved with the people around me...
Rinko had you... so Rinko was able to change.
When I see something like that... I just, you know.
The kindness I received from you... I wish it could be shared with everyone else...
I was thinking that if it were Rinko now... I was wondering if I could give it to someone...
That's how I came up with the band idea... It was on the spot, though.
...I have to apologize to them both.
Besides... it wouldn't be cool if the live show failed because of Rinko, after all her big talk.
Yeah, the gig's gotta be a success！
That's what I'm talking about！ You, too, stay strong！
(Well, it's another day in the band！)
(The atmosphere is as heavy as ever...)
I was late for practice... and I was selfish about changes, songwriting... and many other things.
And then there's... suddenly saying we should have a band！ I was so excited to be involved.
I thought that was a good thing.
I wondered if you were not frustrated that those gals were making fun of you. Then, I thought I would do something about it.
I'll do something about it... I was think that.
...you're making it a big deal... so conceited...
It's not a big deal, but I was so happy, me and my senpai...
With Kobayakawa-san with me, I'm sure I can do my best and... always be the one who can be more proud of myself...
That's why I want to... absolutely make the concert a success. I don't want all the hard work we have done together to go to waste.
I'm not going to run away from it anymore... I really want to do it to the best of my ability...
Yeah, let's do our best... seriously so as not to leave any regrets！
(Rehearsal is coming up soon, and they're not all here yet...)
Oh, good morning. Well, it's finally tomorrow！
(I knew everyone was nervous... me too.)
(We're going to have a live concert here, it's a big place... I wonder how many people will be coming...)
What are you just sitting there like that？
Haha, I was just thinking it's huge！
It's the usual auditorium. Are you scared？
What is it... what's with it... that's why I said it was impossible from the beginning...
Why do I have to watch the rehearsal too？ The show is tomorrow.
It'll be okay. Look, it's starting！
Wrong！ Di Primes isn't just any V-kei！ Look, Hara-Chin, too！
Yeah, I'm going to miss Shin-sama's rehearsal.
Okay, thank you for the show. Now, next band, please.
Drum-san, may I have three points？
Yeah, please give me a proper sound with hat, snare and bass drum.
(Ugh, everyone was a wreck, including me...)
I-I'm sorry... it's my fault... I wanna go home...
This is why... this is why... abominable...
(I hope this will work out for us...)
(Huh... you're speaking with someone today, ▲小早川＊▲...)
The live show, it's about to happen.
You seem to be practicing hard.
Um... I'm not confident, but... well, you can count on me！
Music is not a skill. I'll show you how serious we are.
Hmm, I'm not getting it, but I'm looking forward to it...
(Finally, on this day, the day of the gig！)
Let's all get a hold on！
Rehearsal is rehearsal. Think about it the other way around, you got lucky that it was the rehearsal that failed！
Don't worry, we've been practicing. If I don't do this, those gals will laugh at me again.
